[120.955987, "o", "                                                              \u001b[1;4mClick Onboarding Document\u001b[0m                                                               \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mWhat this repo actually does\u001b[0m                                                                                                                          \r\n\r\nClick is a Python library for creating command-line interfaces (CLIs). It provides decorators and utilities to transform regular Python functions into\r\ncommand-line commands with automatic help generation, parameter validation, type conversion, and rich terminal features.                              \r\n\r\nThe library follows a decorator-based approach where you annotate functions with \u001b[1;36;40m@click.command()\u001b[0m and \u001b[1;36;40m@click.option()\u001b[0m to create CLI commands. It      \r\nhandles argument parsing, type conversion, help text generation, and provides utilities for colored output, progress bars, prompts, and file handling.\r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mHow to run it locally\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                 \r\n\r\nSince this is a library, there's no main application to run. However, you can:                                                                        \r\n\r\n\u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mInstall in development mode:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                       \r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mpip\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235minstall\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m-e\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m.\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                 \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mRun the examples:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                  \r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mcd\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mexamples/colors\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                               \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mpython\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mcolors.py\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                 \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                                 \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mcd\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mexamples/complex\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                              \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mpython\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m-m\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mcomplex\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m--help\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                         \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                  "]
[120.956679, "o", "                 \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mRun tests:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                         \r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;244;48;5;235m# Tests are typically in tests/ directory\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                        \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mpytest\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mtests/\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                    \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mArchitecture: how the pieces connect\u001b[0m                                                                                                                  \r\n\r\nThe architecture is built around several key components:                                                                                              \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mCore Command System (\u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/core.py\u001b[0m\u001b[1m):\u001b[0m                                                                                                              \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mContext\u001b[0m: Holds command execution state and configuration                                                                                           \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mParameter\u001b[0m: Base class for command parameters (options/arguments)                                                                                   \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mCommand\u001b[0m: Represents a single CLI command                                                                                                           \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mGroup\u001b[0m: Container for multiple commands (subcommands)                                                                                               \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mDecorators (\u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/decorators.py\u001b[0m\u001b[1m):\u001b[0m                                                                                                                 \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40m@command()\u001b[0m: Transforms functions into Command objects                                                                                              \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40m@option()\u001b[0m: Adds command-line options to functions                                                                                                  \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40m@argument()\u001b[0m: Adds positional arguments                                                                                                             \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40m@group()\u001b[0m: Creates command groups for subcommands                                                                                                   \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mType System (\u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/types.py\u001b[0m\u001b[1m):\u001b[0m                                                                                                                     \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mParamType\u001b[0m: Base class for parameter type conversion                                                                                                \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mBuilt-in types: \u001b[1;36;40mINT\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mSTRING\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mPath\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mChoice\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mDateTime\u001b[0m, etc.                                                                                          \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mHandles validation and conversion from command-line strings                                                                                        \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mTerminal UI (\u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/termui.py\u001b[0m\u001b[1m):\u001b[0m                                                                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b["]
[120.957234, "o", "1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mecho()\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40msecho()\u001b[0m: Enhanced print functions with color support                                                                                       \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mprompt()\u001b[0m: Interactive user input with validation                                                                                                   \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mprogressbar()\u001b[0m: Progress indicators                                                                                                                 \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mstyle()\u001b[0m: ANSI color and formatting                                                                                                                 \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mFlow:\u001b[0m Function в†’ Decorators в†’ Command/Group в†’ Parser в†’ Type Conversion в†’ Execution                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mCore files to read first (with one-line explanations)\u001b[0m                                                                                                 \r\n\r\n\u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/__init__.py\u001b[0m - Public API exports, shows all available functions and classes                                                              \r\n\u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/decorators.py\u001b[0m - Core decorator functions that users interact with most                                                                   \r\n\u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/core.py\u001b[0m - Command, Group, Context classes that form the execution model                                                                  \r\n\u001b[36m 4 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mexamples/colors/colors.py\u001b[0m - Simple example showing basic usage patterns                                                                            \r\n\u001b[36m 5 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mexamples/complex/complex/cli.py\u001b[0m - Advanced patterns like custom command classes and dynamic loading                                                \r\n\u001b[36m 6 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/types.py\u001b[0m - Parameter type system for validation and conversion                                                                           \r\n\u001b[36m 7 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/termui.py\u001b[0m - Terminal utilities for colors, prompts, progress bars                                                                        \r\n\u001b[36m 8 \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/utils.py\u001b[0m - Utility functions for file handling and output                                                                                \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mKey patterns and conventions\u001b[0m                                                                                                                          \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mDecorator Stacking:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                   \r\n\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                                      \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;148;48;5;235m@click\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;204;48;5;235m.\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mcommand\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m(\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m)\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                    \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;148;48;5;235m@click\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;204;48;5;235m.\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235moption\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m(\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m--verbose\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m,\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m-v\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m,\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mis_flag\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;204;48;5;235m=\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;81;48;5;235mTrue\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m)\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                      \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;148;48;5;235m@click\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;204;48;5;235m.\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235margument\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m(\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;5;235mfilename\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;186;48;"]
[120.957683, "o", "5;235m'\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m)\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                         \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;81;48;5;235mdef\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;148;48;5;235mmycmd\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m(\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mverbose\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m,\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235mfilename\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m)\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m:\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                       \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;231;48;5;235m    \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;81;48;5;235mpass\u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                            \u001b[0m\u001b[48;5;235m \u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[48;5;235m                                                                                                                                                      \u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1mContext Passing:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                      \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mUse \u001b[1;36;40m@click.pass_context\u001b[0m to access the Click context                                                                                                \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mUse \u001b[1;36;40mclick.make_pass_decorator(MyClass, ensure=True)\u001b[0m for dependency injection                                                                       \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mContext objects flow through command hierarchy                                                                                                     \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mCustom Command Classes:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                               \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mExtend \u001b[1;36;40mclick.Group\u001b[0m for dynamic command loading                                                                                                     \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mOverride \u001b[1;36;40mlist_commands()\u001b[0m and \u001b[1;36;40mget_command()\u001b[0m for plugin-style architectures                                                                          \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mParameter Types:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                      \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mAll CLI arguments go through type conversion via \u001b[1;36;40mParamType\u001b[0m subclasses                                                                              \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mCustom types inherit from \u001b[1;36;40mParamType\u001b[0m and implement \u001b[1;36;40mconvert()\u001b[0m                                                                                        \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mEnvironment Variable Integration:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                     \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mParameters automatically map to environment variables                                                                                              \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mUse \u001b[1;36;40mauto_envvar_prefix\u001b[0m in context settings for consistent prefixing                                                                                \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mWhat is undocumented or surprising\u001b[0m                                                                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mDynamic Command Loading:\u001b[0m The complex example shows how to load commands from files at runtime by overriding \u001b[1;36;40mGroup\u001b[0m methods - this pattern isn't     \r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0mobvious from basic usage.                                                                                                                          \r\n\u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mContext Propagation:\u001b[0m The context system automatically flows through command hierarchies, but the \u001b[1;36;40mensure=True\u001b[0m parameter in \u001b[1;36;40mmake_pass_decorator\u001b[0m      \r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0mcreates objects if they don't exist.                                                              "]
[120.958465, "o", "                                                 \r\n\u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mType Conversion Edge Cases:\u001b[0m Type conversion happens even for values that are already the correct type, and converters must handle \u001b[1;36;40mNone\u001b[0m values      \r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0mspecially.                                                                                                                                         \r\n\u001b[36m 4 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mANSI Color Handling:\u001b[0m Colors are automatically stripped when output is redirected to files, but this behavior can be overridden.                    \r\n\u001b[36m 5 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mEnvironment Variable Splitting:\u001b[0m Different parameter types have different default splitting behavior for environment variables (whitespace vs path  \r\n\u001b[36m   \u001b[0mseparators).                                                                                                                                       \r\n\u001b[36m 6 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mCommand Resolution:\u001b[0m Groups can dynamically resolve commands at runtime, enabling plugin architectures and lazy loading.                            \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mWhere to go next\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                      \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mFor Basic Usage:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                      \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mStudy \u001b[1;36;40mexamples/colors/colors.py\u001b[0m for simple commands                                                                                                \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mLook at built-in types in \u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/types.py\u001b[0m                                                                                                       \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mExplore terminal utilities in \u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/termui.py\u001b[0m                                                                                                  \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mFor Advanced Patterns:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mExamine \u001b[1;36;40mexamples/complex/\u001b[0m for dynamic command loading                                                                                              \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mStudy \u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/core.py\u001b[0m Context and Group classes                                                                                                  \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mLook at custom parameter types and validation                                                                                                      \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mFor Contributing:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mCheck the test suite structure                                                                                                                     \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mUnderstand the compatibility layer in \u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/_compat.py\u001b[0m                                                                                         \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mReview exception handling in \u001b[1;36;40msrc/click/exceptions.py\u001b[0m                                                                                               \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mCommon Next Steps:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0mCreate a simple CLI with options and arguments                                                                                                     \r\n\u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0mAdd colored output and progress bars                                                                                                               \r\n\u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0mImplement command groups for subcommands                                                                                                           \r\n\u001b[36m 4 \u001b[0mBuild custom parameter types                                                                                                                       \r\n\u001b[36m 5 \u001b[0"]
[120.95956, "o", "mCreate dynamic command loading for plugins                                                                                                         \r\n\r\n\u001b[4;35mREADME vs reality\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                     \r\n\r\n\u001b[1;35mWhat the source code reveals that the README doesn't mention\u001b[0m                                                                                          \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mComplex type system architecture\u001b[0m: The codebase has an entire \u001b[1;36;40mtypes.py\u001b[0m module with sophisticated parameter types like \u001b[1;36;40mPath\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mChoice\u001b[0m, \u001b[1;36;40mDateTime\u001b[0m, and   \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mTuple\u001b[0m, plus a \u001b[1;36;40mParamType\u001b[0m base class for custom types - none of which are hinted at in the README                                                    \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mRich terminal UI capabilities\u001b[0m: \u001b[1;36;40mtermui.py\u001b[0m provides progress bars, colored output via \u001b[1;36;40msecho()\u001b[0m, interactive prompts, and ANSI styling functions that  \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mmake Click much more than just argument parsing                                                                                                    \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mContext system for state management\u001b[0m: The \u001b[1;36;40mContext\u001b[0m class in \u001b[1;36;40mcore.py\u001b[0m manages execution state, configuration, and object passing between commands using\r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mpatterns like \u001b[1;36;40m@click.pass_context\u001b[0m and \u001b[1;36;40mmake_pass_decorator()\u001b[0m                                                                                        \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mDynamic command loading infrastructure\u001b[0m: The codebase supports plugin-style architectures through custom \u001b[1;36;40mGroup\u001b[0m classes that override \u001b[1;36;40mlist_commands()\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mand \u001b[1;36;40mget_command()\u001b[0m for runtime command discovery                                                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[1;35mWhat the README oversimplifies or skips\u001b[0m                                                                                                               \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1m\"Arbitrary nesting\"\u001b[0m glosses over the sophisticated \u001b[1;36;40mGroup\u001b[0m/\u001b[1;36;40mCommand\u001b[0m hierarchy in \u001b[1;36;40mcore.py\u001b[0m and the complexity of context propagation through nested     \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mcommand structures                                                                                                                                 \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1mEnvironment variable integration\u001b[0m: Parameters automatically map to environment variables with configurable prefixes (\u001b[1;36;40mauto_envvar_prefix\u001b[0m), but this  \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0misn't mentioned despite being a core feature                                                                                                       \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0mThe simple example completely ignores that Click handles type conversion, validation, help generation, and error handling automatically through the\r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0mdecorator system                                                                                                                                   \r\n\u001b[1m вЂў \u001b[0m\u001b[1m\"Lazy loading\"\u001b[0m is mentioned but the README provides no hint of how this works (custom Group subclasses) or that there's a complete example in      \r\n\u001b[1m   \u001b[0m\u001b[1;36;40mexamples/complex/\u001b[0m showing dynamic command loading                                                                                                  \r\n"]
[120.961112, "o", "\r\n\u001b[32mSaved to \u001b[0m\u001b[32m/tmp/\u001b[0m\u001b[32mdemo-out.md\u001b[0m\r\n"]
